						<summary>

						<p>Slab in a field called Kaḷḷi-maru.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya I 1418 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record states that <hi rend="italic">haḍapada</hi> Nagaṁṇa-Oḍeya was governing the Mangalūru-rājya under the orders of Virapratāpa Dēvarāya-mahārāya and refers to Pānḍyapparasa, the younger brother of the Banga Chief (name lost).</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1340, Bhādrapada, ba. 30, Monday. The cyclic year is not mentioned. Probably the given tithi corresponds to 1418 A.D., August 31. [In Śaka 1340 the cyclic year was Viḷambi].</p>						

						</summary>
